At least, three persons were reportedly injured Wednesday afternoon after a gas cylinder exploded in Victoria Island, Lagos. The incident took place at the Four Point by Sheraton Hotel, Oniru in Victoria Island, Lagos at about 12:35 pm It was gathered that one of the cylinder hoses brought by the welders had leakage which triggered the explosion, the Nation reports. According to Director-General, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA) Dr. Femi Oke-Osayintolu confirming the incident said recovery operation was ongoing. He added that several vehicles on the premises, room windows, and other items were shattered. He said: “The situation is under control as a combined effort of the LASEMA Response Unit (LRU), Nigeria Police alongside a staff of the hotel are on ground to ensure a swift recovery. “A total of three people sustained severe injuries as a result of the blast and two have been rushed to Lagos Island General hospital for intensive care by LASEMA Ambulance Unit while one was rushed to a nearby private hospital. “Several cars and hotel room windows were shattered as a result of flying objects due to the blast. Recovery operation ongoing.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.